date: march 5, 2020to: facultyfrom: vincent j. del casino, jr., provost and senior vp for academic affairs and mohamed abousalem, vice president for research and innovationdear faculty,earlier today, a message providingupdates to sjsus response to the continued coronavirus disease 2019 (covid-19) outbreakwas sent to the campus community. this message is meant to provide supplemental information that aligns with centers for disease control (cdc) and the world health organization (who). due to the fact that santa clara county has had community-acquired (i.e. non-travel related) cases of covid-19, we are evaluating teaching practices and research needs.effective immediately, additional precautions need to be taken, including the possibility of temporarily suspending practices in your teaching or current research activities that deal with the use of human fluids such as saliva or urine. those who need to continue these types of activities should follow the cdc guidelines, which include the use of biosafety level-2 containment.please share this message with staff associated with these teaching and research activities.for further information, please contact avp research, pam stacks atpamela.stacks@sjsu.eduor 408-924-2488.sincerely,vincent j. del casino, jr.provost and senior vice president for academic affairsmohamed abousalemvice president for research and innovationphone:408-924-2400email:provost@sjsu.educlark hall 552one washington squaresan jos, ca 95192-0020